HEADWORD: Pneumococcus
<hw>Pneu`mo*coc"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Pneumo-</er>, and <er>Coccus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A
form of micrococcus found in the sputum (and elsewhere) of persons
suffering with pneumonia, and thought to be the cause of this
disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

